FBIS3-31324 "dreeu033_i_94008" FBIS-EEU-94-033 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Feb 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serb General Threatens To Take Hostages AU1702113694 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 1000 GMT 17 Feb 94 AU1702113694 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network Language: German Article Type:BFN [Text] The Bosnian-Serb military leadership has announced that it will take foreigners in Bosnia hostage in case NATO attacks Serb artillery round Sarajevo. The Serbs would also attack all Bosnian enclaves where UN troops are stationed, Serb General Milovanovic said in an interview with a Belgrade newspaper. This would be a kind of international massacre, the general said.
